><A HREF="gc.htm"> Of God and His Creatures</a><hr><p>
Query, whose soul? Apparently, that of the father: for, according to 
St Thomas, the 'formative virtue' of the <i>semen</i> is the father's, 
and as his it remains all throughout the process of formation of the 
body of the embryo.

